dataIdInfo.idAbs: Approximate locations for habitat projects located within the Sacramento-San Joaquin Delta. This project list builds on earlier efforts, including those of DWR, CALFED Ecosystem Restoration Program (ERP), Natural Resources Projects Inventory (NRPI), Wildlife Conservation Board, and other private programs that track restoration projects using GIS. The features consist of acquisitions, planned, and implemented projects that occurred from 1994 through the present. The project boundaries are not surveyed boundaries or derived from legal descriptions, but rather were established using various methods and sources, such as interpretations of rough paper maps provided by project proponents, available institutional knowledge, and interpretations of aerial imagery. Many of the projects are in the planning stages, with some boundaries subject to change. Additionally, some features represent the actual project footprint, while other features represent the entire property boundary.
dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This feature class serves as a planning tool for coordinated restoration in the Sacramento-San Joaquin Delta. The list of habitat projects is part of a broader effort to update information on habitat-related actions in the Sacramento-San Joaquin Delta. In the near term, the intent is to provide a tool to facilitate coordination between State, federal agencies, and stakeholders. The goal is to avoid competition for the same properties, and to locate adjacent projects with conflicting project goals. It will also enhance the ability for planning efforts to consider broader landscape-level restoration goals.
The associated data are considered DWR enterprise GIS data, which meet all appropriate requirements of the DWR Spatial Data Standards, specifically the DWR Spatial Data Standard version 3.1, dated September 11, 2019. DWR makes no warranties or guarantees either expressed or implied as to the completeness, accuracy, or correctness of the data. DWR neither accepts nor assumes liability arising from or for any incorrect, incomplete, or misleading subject data. The official DWR GIS steward for this data set is Arina Ushakova, who may be contacted at 916-653-3639, or at Arina.Ushakova@water.ca.gov. Comments, problems, improvements, updates, or suggestions should be forwarded to the official GIS steward as available and appropriate.
The information included in this dataset is For Official Use Only (FOUO) and should be handled as sensitive information not to be disclosed. This dataset should be safeguarded, handled, transmitted, and stored in accordance with appropriate security directives. No use, reproduction, or disclosure is authorized without the express written permission of the California Department of Water Resources. Unauthorized release may result in criminal and administrative penalties.

report.measDesc: All known projects and project attributes are included, but additions will be expected over time. There is some geographic overlap among project polygons that is likely not present in reality.

The data are considered complete within the project footprint. However, updates in the future may reveal that this version is missing some projects we are unaware of. Currently, data from FESSRO is included, but many others DWR programs could be included. Therefore, this information will be added as feasible.

The habitat project features were digitized from a variety of sources, with their inclusion being decided upon by project leader, Anitra Pawley. The features and their names have been reviewed by several environmental scientists, and all are in agreement that the project titles are correct.

Locational Quality: Locational quality determined to be no better than 101.987 meters at 90% confidence level as determined by a test comparison with 2012 NAIP imagery (NAIP accuracy stated as 6 meters). This report is not being made by a licensed land surveyor, and is not analogous to a positional accuracy statement as stipulated in the California Public Resources Code.
